title: Cherokee Nation announces plans for $18M Oklahoma drug treatment center
description: With Native Americans disproportionately affected by opioid addiction, Cherokee Nation of Oklahoma has announced plans for an $18 million addiction center.

title: Austin Majors, 'NYPD Blue' child actor, dead at 27
description: Austin Majors, the child star who appeared in "NYPD Blue" as Theo Sipowicz, has died. His sister, Kali, took to Facebook on Sunday to share a collage of memories with her older brother.

title: Nets blame Kyrie Irving for their 'Big Three' with Kevin Durant, James Harden not working out: report
description: While the Brooklyn Nets are moving forward since trading away their three all-stars who were supposed to form a superteam, they reportedly blame Kyrie Irving in particular for that.

title: CDC reports 60% increases in high school girls seriously considering or planning suicide, sadness
description: A Center for Disease Control report published Monday showed increased suicidal thoughts among high school aged girls and poor mental health over all.

title: Cheerleader gets ejected after on-court altercation with college basketball player
description: A game between Mississippi Valley State and Alabama A&M ended in a buzzer beater for the win, but that wasn't even the wildest part of the night. A cheerleader was ejected prior.

title: Face masks made ‘little to no difference’ in spread of COVID, scientific review finds
description: A new scientific review suggests that mask mandates, per the CDC's recommendations, may have done little to nothing to curb the transmission of COVID.

title: You can't 'invade' America's sovereign airspace: Montana GOP Senator
description: Sen. Steve Daine, R-Mont., gives his take on recent aerial objects that have entered U.S. airspace on 'The Story with Martha MacCallum.'

title: FOX Sports’ Super Bowl LVII draws 113 million viewers for six-year high
description: FOX Sports’ presentation of Super Bowl LVII drew 113 million viewers as the Kansas City Chiefs topped the Philadelphia Eagles 38-35 from State Farm Stadium in Glendale, Arizona.

title: House GOP demands answers from Pentagon on leaked records of Jennifer-Ruth Green's sexual assault
description: House Republicans are demanding answers from Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin over leaked personnel records that led to the outing of Jennifer-Ruth Green as a sexual assault survivor.

title: Jessie James Decker, Eric Decker enjoy weekend getaway with cheeky snapshots in the snow and topless painting
description: Jessie James Decker and Eric Decker shared a video of their romantic Valentine's weekend getaway, with the singer occasionally going topless and showing some skin.

title: 'Drug' journalist lambasted after calling to 'destigmatise chemsex': 'Do I want to know what that means?'
description: Author and journalist Michelle Lhooq’s article defended the merits of “chemsex” or engaging in casual and group sex while using substances, in an article on Monday.
